<div class="rimage default"><img decoding="async" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20250518100700im_/https://r-nimble.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/results-CRPalpha2-1.png" class="plot"/></div>
<div class="rcode">
<div class="source">
<pre class="knitr r"><span class="hl com"># Histogram of the posterior samples for the concentration parameter </span>
<span class="hl kwd">hist</span><span class="hl std">(samples[ ,</span> <span class="hl str">'alpha'</span><span class="hl std">],</span> <span class="hl kwc">xlab</span> <span class="hl std">=</span> <span class="hl kwd">expression</span><span class="hl std">(alpha),</span> <span class="hl kwc">ylab</span> <span class="hl std">=</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;Frequency&quot;</span><span class="hl std">,</span> <span class="hl kwc">main</span> <span class="hl std">=</span> <span class="hl str">&quot;&quot;</span><span class="hl std">)</span>
</pre>
</div>
</div>
<div class="rimage default"><img decoding="async" src="https://web.archive.org/web/20250518100700im_/https://r-nimble.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/results-CRPalpha2-2.png" class="plot"/></div>
</div>
<h3> Generating samples from the mixing distribution</h3>
<p>As before, we obtain samples from the posterior distribution of <img src="https://web.archive.org/web/20250518100700im_/https://s0.wp.com/latex.php?latex=G&amp;bg=ffffff&amp;fg=000000&amp;s=0" alt="G" title="G" class="latex"/> using the <tt>getSamplesDPmeasure</tt> function. </p>
